messages:
Name: Fred
Nationality: Brazil
Date of Birth: March 5, 1993
Position: Midfielder
Current club: Manchester United
Premier League clubs played for: Manchester United

Manchester United midfielder Fred has taken part in the vast majority of the side's Premier League matches in 2022/2023, making 35 appearances overall and accumulating 1,232 minutes of playing time. He has been selected in the starting XI in 12 of these appearances across their 38 fixtures and been mainly used off the bench as a substitute on 23 occasions.

Fred last appeared in a competition match on May 28 for Manchester United against Fulham. In that game the 30-year-old picked up one assist for his side in the side's 2-1 win. In total, he has notched two Premier League goals this term, and registered two assists. He has amassed six yellow cards.

Fred last scored in the league in the 3-0 win against Nottingham Forest on December 27, netting in the 87th minute. He opened his account for the campaign against Tottenham Hotspur on October 19, scoring during a 2-0 victory.
Last season for Manchester United, Fred made 28 Premier League appearances, scored four goals and provided four assists.
Fred switched to Manchester United in June 2018 from Shakhtar Donetsk, for whom he made 101 league appearances in total, scoring 10 goals and providing 11 assists.

It was on August 10, 2018 that Fred made his league debut, at the age of 25 years and 158 days, versus Leicester City. In his Premier League career overall, he has played 139 times in the competition, with eight goals and seven assists.
